name: NES/C64 Mod Kit
description: This kit is new, and never installed. I have one left for sale. Created by low-gain Electronics This kit Adds two 1/4" jacks to your NES. The new source will provide a mildly boosted audio output and "faux" stereo sound for the NES console. The Pulse channels are output on the left side and triangle/wave/noise channels are output on the right side. If only the left output is used, all channels are summed to mono on this output. This circuit also provides protection to your NES's main board from reverse voltage spikes. This kit includes an assembled PCB and hook-up wires for easy installation. instructions on installation can be found here.
